import pandas as pd
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
import pytz

# Define the time range in UTC+8
start_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 20, 30, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Hong_Kong'))
end_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 21, 0, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Hong_Kong'))

# Convert to UTC timestamps (seconds)
start_timestamp = int(start_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())
end_timestamp = int(end_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())

# Load service metrics
service_metrics = pd.read_csv('dataset/Market/cloudbed-2/telemetry/2022_03_21/metric/metric_service.csv')

# Filter data within the time range
service_metrics_filtered = service_metrics[
    (service_metrics['timestamp'] >= start_timestamp) & 
    (service_metrics['timestamp'] <= end_timestamp)
]

# Calculate baseline metrics for each service (using data from 20:00-20:30 as baseline)
baseline_start = int(start_time_utc8 - timedelta(minutes=30)).timestamp()
baseline_end = start_timestamp
baseline_data = service_metrics[
    (service_metrics['timestamp'] >= baseline_start) & 
    (service_metrics['timestamp'] <= baseline_end)
]
baseline_stats = baseline_data.groupby('service').agg({
    'rr': ['mean', 'std'],
    'sr': ['mean', 'std'],
    'mrt': ['mean', 'std'],
    'count': ['mean', 'std']
}).reset_index()
baseline_stats.columns = ['service', 'rr_mean', 'rr_std', 'sr_mean', 'sr_std', 'mrt_mean', 'mrt_std', 'count_mean', 'count_std']

# Merge baseline stats with filtered data
anomaly_analysis = pd.merge(service_metrics_filtered, baseline_stats, on='service')

# Identify anomalies (3 standard deviations from baseline)
anomaly_analysis['rr_anomaly'] = abs(anomaly_analysis['rr'] - anomaly_analysis['rr_mean']) > 3 * anomaly_analysis['rr_std']
anomaly_analysis['sr_anomaly'] = abs(anomaly_analysis['sr'] - anomaly_analysis['sr_mean']) > 3 * anomaly_analysis['sr_std']
anomaly_analysis['mrt_anomaly'] = abs(anomaly_analysis['mrt'] - anomaly_analysis['mrt_mean']) > 3 * anomaly_analysis['mrt_std']
anomaly_analysis['count_anomaly'] = abs(anomaly_analysis['count'] - anomaly_analysis['count_mean']) > 3 * anomaly_analysis['count_std']

# Convert timestamps back to UTC+8 for readability
anomaly_analysis['datetime_utc8'] = pd.to_datetime(anomaly_analysis['timestamp'], unit='s').dt.tz_localize('utc').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Hong_Kong')

# Show services with any anomalies
services_with_anomalies = anomaly_analysis[
    anomaly_analysis['rr_anomaly'] | 
    anomaly_analysis['sr_anomaly'] | 
    anomaly_analysis['mrt_anomaly'] | 
    anomaly_analysis['count_anomaly']
][['service', 'datetime_utc8', 'rr', 'sr', 'mrt', 'count', 'rr_anomaly', 'sr_anomaly', 'mrt_anomaly', 'count_anomaly']].sort_values(['service', 'datetime_utc8'])

print("Services with anomalies during 20:30-21:00 UTC+8:")
print(services_with_anomalies.to_string(index=False))

import pandas as pd
import pytz
from datetime import datetime

# Define the time range in UTC+8
start_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 20, 30, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Shanghai'))
end_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 21, 0, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Shanghai'))

# Convert to UTC timestamps (seconds)
start_timestamp = int(start_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())
end_timestamp = int(end_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())

# Load service metrics
service_metrics = pd.read_csv('dataset/Market/cloudbed-2/telemetry/2022_03_21/metric/metric_service.csv')

# Calculate global thresholds (P5 and P95) for each KPI across all services and all times
global_thresholds = {
    'rr_p5': service_metrics['rr'].quantile(0.05),
    'rr_p95': service_metrics['rr'].quantile(0.95),
    'sr_p5': service_metrics['sr'].quantile(0.05),
    'sr_p95': service_metrics['sr'].quantile(0.95),
    'mrt_p5': service_metrics['mrt'].quantile(0.05),
    'mrt_p95': service_metrics['mrt'].quantile(0.95),
    'count_p5': service_metrics['count'].quantile(0.05),
    'count_p95': service_metrics['count'].quantile(0.95)
}

# Filter data within the time range
service_metrics_filtered = service_metrics[
    (service_metrics['timestamp'] >= start_timestamp) & 
    (service_metrics['timestamp'] <= end_timestamp)
].copy()

# Convert timestamps to UTC+8 datetime
service_metrics_filtered['datetime_utc8'] = pd.to_datetime(service_metrics_filtered['timestamp'], unit='s')
service_metrics_filtered['datetime_utc8'] = service_metrics_filtered['datetime_utc8'].dt.tz_localize('utc').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Shanghai')

# Identify anomalies
anomalies = []
for _, row in service_metrics_filtered.iterrows():
    anomaly = {
        'service': row['service'],
        'datetime_utc8': row['datetime_utc8'],
        'rr': row['rr'],
        'sr': row['sr'],
        'mrt': row['mrt'],
        'count': row['count'],
        'anomaly_type': []
    }
    
    if row['rr'] < global_thresholds['rr_p5']:
        anomaly['anomaly_type'].append(f'rr < P5 ({global_thresholds["rr_p5"]:.2f})')
    if row['sr'] < global_thresholds['sr_p5']:
        anomaly['anomaly_type'].append(f'sr < P5 ({global_thresholds["sr_p5"]:.2f})')
    if row['mrt'] > global_thresholds['mrt_p95']:
        anomaly['anomaly_type'].append(f'mrt > P95 ({global_thresholds["mrt_p95"]:.2f})')
    if row['count'] < global_thresholds['count_p5']:
        anomaly['anomaly_type'].append(f'count < P5 ({global_thresholds["count_p5"]:.2f})')
    
    if anomaly['anomaly_type']:
        anomalies.append(anomaly)

# Convert anomalies to DataFrame
anomalies_df = pd.DataFrame(anomalies)
if not anomalies_df.empty:
    anomalies_df['anomaly_type'] = anomalies_df['anomaly_type'].apply(lambda x: ', '.join(x))
    print("Anomalies detected in service metrics between 20:30 and 21:00 UTC+8:")
    print(anomalies_df.to_string(index=False))
else:
    print("No anomalies detected in service metrics between 20:30 and 21:00 UTC+8.")

# Store thresholds and filtered data for future use
global_thresholds, service_metrics_filtered

# Check if there are any rows with sr < sr_p5 or mrt > mrt_p95 in the filtered data
anomalies_detected = service_metrics_filtered[
    (service_metrics_filtered['sr'] < global_thresholds['sr_p5']) |
    (service_metrics_filtered['mrt'] > global_thresholds['mrt_p95'])
]

print(f"Number of anomalies detected: {len(anomalies_detected)}")
print("\nAnomalies details:")
anomalies_detected[['service', 'datetime_utc8', 'sr', 'mrt']].sort_values('datetime_utc8')

from datetime import datetime

# Define the time range in UTC+8

end_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 21, 0, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Shanghai'))

start_timestamp = int(start_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())
end_timestamp = int(end_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())

container_metrics = pd.read_csv('dataset/Market/cloudbed-2/telemetry/2022_03_21/metric/metric_container.csv')

# Filter data for checkoutservice pods
checkout_containers = container_metrics[
    container_metrics['cmdb_id'].str.contains('checkoutservice') &
    (container_metrics['timestamp'] >= start_timestamp) &
    (container_metrics['timestamp'] <= end_timestamp)
]

# Filter for relevant KPIs: CPU usage, memory usage, disk I/O
relevant_kpis = [
    'container_cpu_usage_seconds',
    'container_memory_usage_MB',
    'container_fs_reads_MB./dev/vda',
    'container_fs_writes_MB./dev/vda'
]
checkout_metrics_filtered = checkout_containers[checkout_containers['kpi_name'].isin(relevant_kpis)]

# Calculate global thresholds for each relevant KPI
kpi_thresholds = {}
for kpi in relevant_kpis:
    kpi_data = container_metrics[container_metrics['kpi_name'] == kpi]['value']
    kpi_thresholds[kpi] = {
        'p95': kpi_data.quantile(0.95),
        'p5': kpi_data.quantile(0.05)
    }

# Convert timestamps to UTC+8 datetime
checkout_metrics_filtered['datetime_utc8'] = pd.to_datetime(checkout_metrics_filtered['timestamp'], unit='s')
checkout_metrics_filtered['datetime_utc8'] = checkout_metrics_filtered['datetime_utc8'].dt.tz_localize('utc').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Shanghai')

# Identify anomalies
anomalies = []
for _, row in checkout_metrics_filtered.iterrows():
    threshold = kpi_thresholds[row['kpi_name']]
    anomaly = None
    
    # For CPU, memory, and disk writes, we look for values above P95
    if row['kpi_name'] in ['container_cpu_usage_seconds', 'container_memory_usage_MB', 'container_fs_writes_MB./dev/vda']:
        if row['value'] > threshold['p95']:
            anomaly = f"{row['kpi_name']} > P95 ({threshold['p95']:.2f})"
    # For disk reads, we look for values above P95 as well
    elif row['kpi_name'] == 'container_fs_reads_MB./dev/vda':
        if row['value'] > threshold['p95']:
            anomaly = f"{row['kpi_name']} > P95 ({threshold['p95']:.2f})"
    
    if anomaly:
        anomalies.append({
            'cmdb_id': row['cmdb_id'],
            'datetime_utc8': row['datetime_utc8'],
            'kpi_name': row['kpi_name'],
            'value': row['value'],
            'anomaly_type': anomaly
        })

# Convert anomalies to DataFrame
anomalies_df = pd.DataFrame(anomalies)
if not anomalies_df.empty:
    print("Anomalies detected in checkoutservice container metrics between 20:30 and 21:00 UTC+8:")
    print(anomalies_df.sort_values(['datetime_utc8', 'cmdb_id']).to_string(index=False))
else:
    print("No anomalies detected in checkoutservice container metrics between 20:30 and 21:00 UTC+8.")

# Also check network metrics for checkoutservice pods
network_kpis = [
    'container_network_receive_packets_dropped.eth0',
    'container_network_transmit_packets_dropped.eth0',
    'container_network_receive_errors.eth0',
    'container_network_transmit_errors.eth0'
]
checkout_network_metrics = checkout_containers[checkout_containers['kpi_name'].isin(network_kpis)]

# Check for any non-zero network errors/drops
network_issues = checkout_network_metrics[checkout_network_metrics['value'] > 0]
if not network_issues.empty:
    print("\nNetwork issues detected in checkoutservice pods:")
    print(network_issues[['cmdb_id', 'datetime_utc8', 'kpi_name', 'value']].sort_values('datetime_utc8').to_string(index=False))
else:
    print("\nNo network issues detected in checkoutservice pods.")

import pandas as pd
import pytz
from datetime import datetime

# Define the time range in UTC+8
start_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 20, 30, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Shanghai'))
end_time_utc8 = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 21, 0, 0, tzinfo=pytz.timezone('Asia/Shanghai'))

# Convert to UTC timestamps (seconds)
start_timestamp = int(start_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())
end_timestamp = int(end_time_utc8.astimezone(pytz.utc).timestamp())

# Load trace data
trace_data = pd.read_csv('dataset/Market/cloudbed-2/telemetry/2022_03_21/trace/trace_span.csv')

# Convert trace timestamps from milliseconds to seconds
trace_data['timestamp_seconds'] = trace_data['timestamp'] // 1000

# Filter trace data within the time range
filtered_traces = trace_data[
    (trace_data['timestamp_seconds'] >= start_timestamp) &
    (trace_data['timestamp_seconds'] <= end_timestamp)
]

# Convert timestamps to UTC+8 datetime
filtered_traces['datetime_utc8'] = pd.to_datetime(filtered_traces['timestamp'], unit='ms')
filtered_traces['datetime_utc8'] = filtered_traces['datetime_utc8'].dt.tz_localize('utc').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Shanghai')

# Find traces with checkoutservice spans that have high duration
# First, get the global P95 threshold for span duration
global_p95_duration = trace_data['duration'].quantile(0.95)

# Find checkoutservice spans with duration exceeding P95
slow_checkout_spans = filtered_traces[
    filtered_traces['cmdb_id'].str.contains('checkoutservice') &
    (filtered_traces['duration'] > global_p95_duration)
]

# Group by trace ID to see the full context of slow traces
slow_trace_ids = slow_checkout_spans['trace_id'].unique()
full_slow_traces = filtered_traces[filtered_traces['trace_id'].isin(slow_trace_ids)]

# For each slow trace, find the service with the longest duration
slow_trace_analysis = []
for trace_id in slow_trace_ids:
    trace_spans = full_slow_traces[full_slow_traces['trace_id'] == trace_id]
    max_duration_span = trace_spans[trace_spans['duration'] == trace_spans['duration'].max()].iloc[0]
    
    slow_trace_analysis.append({
        'trace_id': trace_id,
        'datetime_utc8': max_duration_span['datetime_utc8'],
        'slowest_service': max_duration_span['cmdb_id'],
        'operation': max_duration_span['operation_name'],
        'duration_ms': max_duration_span['duration'],
        'status_code': max_duration_span['status_code']
    })

# Convert to DataFrame
slow_trace_df = pd.DataFrame(slow_trace_analysis)
print("Slow traces involving checkoutservice:")
